image_analysis.description: A photograph of a utility or mechanical room, likely in a basement. The room features white walls, a light-colored floor, and various electrical and HVAC components. On the left wall, there are several gray electrical boxes, conduits, and a four-outlet orange power receptacle. A framed document is mounted on the wall near more electrical panels. In the center, an open white door leads to a hallway with patterned flooring. Above, there are large metal air ducts and several white insulated pipes running across the ceiling. A white wall-mounted telephone is visible near the door frame.
